sentences: Charles Shaar Murray (born Charles Maximillian Murray; 27 June 1951) is an English music journalist and broadcaster.
His first experience in journalism came in 1970, when he was one of a number of schoolchildren who responded to an invitation to edit the April issue of the satirical magazine Oz.

He then wrote for IT (International Times), before moving to the New Musical Express in 1972 for which he wrote until around 1986.
